{
  "stem": "11964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But our kitchen was really very interesting, because my-- my mother prided herself on being a very good homemaker.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we had a very large kitchen, I would say at least 20 by 20.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And what very unusual about the kitchen was that it had mahogany floors that were constantly pasted and shined with a-- with a special machine.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there my mother would cook and bake.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in the kitchen, we had, of course, all the service, the china service.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We had a big credenza that held two sets, of course, of dishes, one for meat dishes and one for dairy dishes, and the same thing with-- with silverware.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had all kinds of preparation tables for baking and cooking, a stove, which was-- which was a coal stove, and a bin, which had a surface for baking, which that bin held the coal for the stove.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a bed, and the bed was for our maid, and she would sleep in the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went to that school I mentioned, and most of our friends were the children who actually went to the same school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were children of, again, I must mention this, of middle-class merchants.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the reason that there was a class distinction is because the others could not afford the education.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was something which I still feel was very sad for our Jewish community, because some of the Jewish children could not avail themselves of the good education that some of us did.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Our--our relationships were really connected mostly-- the children were mostly friendly through school and schoolwork and the school activities, and also through the relationships that my parents had with their friends.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My parents would get together with their friends, mostly during the holidays and on the Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
